00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:50.000
Coach: That's a great point. You can also emphasize how the new curriculum addresses individual student needs. Does it offer differentiation options or personalized learning pathways?

00:08:51.000 --> 00:09:05.000
Maria: Yes, it does. It provides a variety of resources and activities that can be adapted to different learning styles and levels.  There are also extension activities for students who need more challenge and support materials for those who need extra help.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:20.000
Coach: Excellent.  Those are definitely key benefits worth highlighting.  And you can also mention how the new curriculum ultimately leads to better learning outcomes.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:35.000
Maria: Right. We've seen some promising data from other schools that have already implemented the curriculum. They've reported increased student engagement, higher test scores, and improved critical thinking skills.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:50.000
Coach: That's fantastic. Sharing that data can be very persuasive.  It gives the teacher concrete evidence of the positive impact the curriculum can have on their students.

00:09:51.000 --> 00:10:05.000
Maria: I'll definitely make sure to include that in our conversation.  I think it will be helpful for the teacher to see the bigger picture and understand how this curriculum can benefit their students.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:20.000
Coach:  Absolutely.  And don't forget to offer your support.  Let the teacher know that you're there to help them with any challenges they might face during the implementation process.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:35.000
